UML:Comment.name: Specializes the standard UML Stereotype file. Indicates that the Artifact represents a JAR.
Indicates that the supplier of the Dependency, a JAR , Java .class file, or other file, is included by value? (i.e., copied into) the JAR that is the client of the Dependency
Indicates that the supplier is a model element that is not contained in the archive but is referenced by it in the META-INF/MANIFEST.MF file
A Boolean value indicating whether or not the Java Field is volatile.
A comma-delimited list of names of Java Exception Classes.
A Boolean value indicating whether or not the Parameter is final.
A Boolean value indicating whether or not the Java Class is FP-strict
A String containing the name of the Java Collection Type used to implement an Attribute or Association End with complex multiplicity.
An Integer indicating the number of array dimensions declared by the Java Field or Parameter.
A Boolean value indicating whether or not the Java Class is static.
A Boolean value indicating whether or not the Operation or Method is native.
